Here's how to handle each scenario with MSTest:

**1. Windows-only tests** — use `[TestCategory]` + conditional skip:

```csharp
[TestMethod]
[TestCategory("WindowsOnly")]
[System.Runtime.Versioning.SupportedOSPlatform("windows")]
public void Registry_ReadsExpectedValue()
{
    if (!OperatingSystem.IsWindows())
        Assert.Inconclusive("Requires Windows.");
    // ... registry code
}
```

**2. Skip in CI** — check an environment variable:

```csharp
[TestMethod]
[TestCategory("RequiresGPU")]
public void Model_RunsOnGpu()
{
    if (Environment.GetEnvironmentVariable("CI") == "true")
        Assert.Inconclusive("Skipped in CI — requires local GPU.");
    // ... GPU test
}
```

**3. Flaky test retry** — use `[Retry]` (MSTest 3.x+):

```csharp
[TestMethod]
[Retry(3)] // retries up to 3 times on failure
public void Weather_ReturnsForecast()
{
    var result = _weatherClient.GetForecast();
    Assert.IsNotNull(result);
}
```

**4. Cleanup even on failure** — use `[TestCleanup]` or `try/finally`:

```csharp
private string _tempFile;

[TestInitialize]
public void Setup() => _tempFile = Path.GetTempFileName();

[TestCleanup] // runs even if the test fails
public void Cleanup()
{
    if (File.Exists(_tempFile))
        File.Delete(_tempFile);
}

[TestMethod]
public void Export_WritesToFile()
{
    File.WriteAllText(_tempFile, "data");
    Assert.IsTrue(new FileInfo(_tempFile).Length > 0);
}
```

---

**Key points:**

| Scenario | Mechanism |
|----------|-----------|
| OS-specific | `Assert.Inconclusive()` + runtime check |
| Skip in CI | Environment variable check |
| Flaky/retry | `[Retry(N)]` attribute (MSTest v3+) |
| Guaranteed cleanup | `[TestCleanup]` method |

You can also filter at the runner level with `dotnet test --filter "TestCategory!=RequiresGPU"` to skip categories entirely in your CI pipeline.
